<p class="has-text-align-center is-style-constrained-paragraph"><strong>Headspace Ballarat</strong> &#8211; Wungurrwil-ngitj (Stronger Together) &#8211; An art and cultural education session was facilitated with the Youth Justice Group at Headspace Ballarat, creating a culturally safe and collaborative space for young people to share stories, perspectives, and how they wished to be represented. Guided by colour, culture, and storytelling, these contributions informed the development of a final artwork, later transformed into a mural for the new Headspace Ballarat offices—reflecting connection to Country, community strength, and the journeys walked <span class="noWidow">every day.</span></p>


