<p class="has-text-align-center is-style-constrained-paragraph"><strong>Serendip Sanctuary Gardens</strong> &#8211; Artwork was created for totem poles and signage across the five sensory spaces at the Serendip Sensory Gardens for Parks Victoria—see, smell, listen, taste, and feel—supporting a place of calm, connection, and inclusive engagement with nature. Each design was thoughtfully linked to its sensory environment, such as Murnong (yam daisy) featured in the taste space and magpie tracks in the listen space, inviting visitors to connect with and learn about Wadawurrung culture while experiencing <span class="noWidow">the gardens.</span></p>


